  "raw_response": "{\n  \"title\": \"July 10, 2023 Swing Low Comparison: NQ made lower low while ES held higher, signaling relative weakness in NQ and strength in ES\",\n  \"school\": \"ICT\",\n  \"asset\": \"NQ1! / ES1!\",\n  \"timeframe\": \"1D\",\n  \"market_context\": \"Daily price action in late July 2023; analyst compared swing lows on Monday, July 10 between correlated indices ES and NQ to assess relative strength/weakness using SMT.\",\n  \"key_observation\": \"On July 10, NQ formed a new swing low while ES did not reach its prior swing low, creating an SMT divergence indicating NQ weakness and ES relative strength.\",\n  \"analysis_steps\": [\n    \"Step 1: The analyst identified the swing point on Monday, July 10, 2023 on the daily chart for both ES1! and NQ1!.\",\n    \"Step 2: He observed that NQ made a lower low on that day, while ES remained significantly above its prior swing low.\",\n    \"Step 3: He interpreted this divergence as an SMT (Smart Money Technique) signal showing relative weakness in NQ and relative strength in ES.\",\n    \"Step 4: He confirmed this by referencing the ES/NQ ratio chart, noting that a bullish ratio aligns with ES strength and NQ weakness.\"\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": null,\n  \"lessons\": \"Comparing swing lows (or highs) across correlated assets reveals relative strength/weakness; a failure to make a new low/high while the counterpart does signals SMT and informs bias selection.\",\n  \"primary_image_frame_id\": \"c_mh19e3mhI_f012\",\n  \"supporting_image_frame_ids\": [\"c_mh19e3mhI_f007\", \"c_mh19e3mhI_f009\"],\n  \"r",
